  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors. This package references the hemolysis modelling methodology published by Morrison et al. (2024) via a DOI-based identifier; that identifier is cited as a referencesIdentifier to anchor the model-form rationale but the corresponding bibliographic node is not declared within this package graph.",
