    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite seven of thirteen credibility factors achieving levels below their MRL-5 required levels and six factors remaining unassessed, the credibility assessment team accepted the package on the basis that Monte Carlo UQ bounds conservatively envelope the clinical hemolysis threshold across the validated operating envelope. The methodology is anchored to the peer-reviewed hemolysis modelling framework cited in the package (Morrison et al., 2024, Methods journal), and residual gaps are acknowledged as subject to post-market surveillance. The decision is accepted with conditions pending independent solver error and use-error quantification in the next assessment cycle.",
